------------------------------------------------------------------
KEY LESSON
------------------------------------------------------------------

Steganography in JPEGs often hides data after the FF D9 EOF
marker. binwalk will find it automatically and extract nested
archives. Password hints are almost always visible in the
challenge description. After any extraction, always check
metadata with exiftool before doing anything else -- the flag
is often sitting in a comment field waiting to be read.
